TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Lagrangean Relaxation Approach for Very-Large-Scale Capacitated Lot-Sizing
AU  - Diaby, Moustapha
AU  - Bahl, Harish C.
AU  - Karwan, Mark H.
AU  - Zionts, Stanley
Y1  - 1992/09/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.38.9.1329
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.38.9.1329
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1329
EP  - 1340
VL  - 38
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In this paper, we develop a Lagrangean relaxation-based heuristic procedure to generate near-optimal solutions to very-large-scale capacitated lot-sizing problems (CLSP) with setup times and limited overtime. Our computational results show that large problems involving several thousand products and several thousand 0/1 integer variables can be solved in a reasonable amount of computer time to within one percent of their optimal solution. The proposed procedure is general enough to be applied directly or with slight modification to real-life production problems.
AB  - In this paper, we develop a Lagrangean relaxation-based heuristic procedure to generate near-optimal solutions to very-large-scale capacitated lot-sizing problems (CLSP) with setup times and limited overtime. Our computational results show that large problems involving several thousand products and several thousand 0/1 integer variables can be solved in a reasonable amount of computer time to within one percent of their optimal solution. The proposed procedure is general enough to be applied directly or with slight modification to real-life production problems.
