TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Operator Assignment and the Parametric Preflow Algorithm
AU  - Wittrock, Robert J.
Y1  - 1992/09/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.38.9.1354
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.38.9.1354
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1354
EP  - 1359
VL  - 38
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This note addresses a problem of assigning human operators to operations in a manufacturing system. The problem involves a set of operations, a work load for each operation, and a set of human operators, each skilled at a subset of the operations. The task is to assign the operators to the operations so as to maximize the capacity of the system, robustly. The problem is formulated as a network flow problem with a lexicographic objective. It is then shown how to solve this problem very efficiently as a parametric sequence of network maximum flow problems, by application of the ?parametric preflow? algorithm of Gallo, Grigoriadis and Tarjan.
AB  - This note addresses a problem of assigning human operators to operations in a manufacturing system. The problem involves a set of operations, a work load for each operation, and a set of human operators, each skilled at a subset of the operations. The task is to assign the operators to the operations so as to maximize the capacity of the system, robustly. The problem is formulated as a network flow problem with a lexicographic objective. It is then shown how to solve this problem very efficiently as a parametric sequence of network maximum flow problems, by application of the ?parametric preflow? algorithm of Gallo, Grigoriadis and Tarjan.
